OL,5,FThe basic procedures were clear to
OL,6,Fevery network director and announcer.
OL,7,FThe announcer calmly apologised, played
OL,8,Fmusic if the problem persisted and 
OL,9,Fwhen appropriate  kept viewers across
OL,10,Fthe situation. It was taken seriously.
OL,12,FDuring a high-profile breakdown, one
OL,13,Fexperienced announcer couldn't get the
OL,14,Fstandby music to start and made a joke
OL,15,Fabout it. It may have seemed human but
OL,16,Fsuch was Presentation's concern for the
OL,17,FBBC's reputation that he got told off.
OL,19,FSadly, this morning on BBC One the
OL,20,Fsituation looked awful.
