OL,5,FBut the editorial procedures for
OL,6,Fhandling breakdowns during live
OL,7,Fprogrammes would seem to be in need of
OL,8,Freview  even if, thankfully, serious
OL,9,Fbreakdowns are now rare.
OL,11,FIt's true that the output of the
OL,12,Fgallery at NBH was still reaching
OL,13,Fplayout but does that excuse the
OL,14,Fshambles that viewers to the nation's
OL,15,Fpremier channel witnessed?
OL,17,FImagine it's 1992. A live OB during
OL,18,FGrandstand goes down, Des Lyman has
OL,19,Fnipped away for a few moments  the
OL,20,Fblack screen from the OB goes to air.
